# Callback Props

When a callback prop is passed in to **all instances** of a component, declare it as **required**, not optional.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — optional when always provided
interface EditorToolbarProps {
  onInsertImage?: () => void;
}

// ✅ GOOD — required when always provided
interface EditorToolbarProps {
  onInsertImage: () => void;
}
```

Use `?` only when the prop is legitimately sometimes absent (e.g. different parents pass different props).
